   323Ôćĺ## [0.4.0] - 2017-12-24
   324Ôćĺ
   325ÔćĺThe changes in this release include cleanup of some obscure functionality and a more robust public
   326ÔćĺAPI designed to support bridges to other logging systems, and provide more flexibility to new
   327Ôćĺfeatures in the future.
   329Ôćĺ### Compatibility
   330Ôćĺ
   331ÔćĺVast portions of the Rust ecosystem use the 0.3.x release series of log, and we don't want to force
   332Ôćĺthe community to go through the pain of upgrading every crate to 0.4.x at the exact same time. Along
   333Ôćĺwith 0.4.0, we've published a new 0.3.9 release which acts as a "shim" over 0.4.0. This will allow
   334Ôćĺcrates using either version to coexist without losing messages from one side or the other.
   345Ôćĺ### New
   346Ôćĺ
   347Ôćĺ* The crate is now `no_std` by default.
   348Ôćĺ* `Level` and `LevelFilter` now implement `Serialize` and `Deserialize` when the `serde` feature is
   349Ôćĺ    enabled.
   350Ôćĺ* The `Record` and `Metadata` types can now be constructed by third-party code via a builder API.
   351Ôćĺ* The `logger` free function returns a reference to the logger implementation. This, along with the
   352Ôćĺ    ability to construct `Record`s, makes it possible to bridge from another logging framework to
   353Ôćĺ    this one without digging into the private internals of the crate. The standard `error!` `warn!`,
   354Ôćĺ    etc., macros now exclusively use the public API of the crate rather than "secret" internal APIs.
   355Ôćĺ* `Log::flush` has been added to allow crates to tell the logging implementation to ensure that all
   356Ôćĺ    "in flight" log events have been persisted. This can be used, for example, just before an
   357Ôćĺ    application exits to ensure that asynchronous log sinks finish their work.
   359Ôćĺ### Removed
   360Ôćĺ
   361Ôćĺ* The `shutdown` and `shutdown_raw` functions have been removed. Supporting shutdown significantly
   362Ôćĺ    complicated the implementation and imposed a performance cost on each logging operation.
   363Ôćĺ* The `log_panics` function and its associated `nightly` Cargo feature have been removed. Use the
   364Ôćĺ    [log-panics](https://crates.io/crates/log-panics) instead.
   366Ôćĺ### Changed
   367Ôćĺ
   368Ôćĺ* The `Log` prefix has been removed from type names. For example, `LogLevelFilter` is now
   369Ôćĺ    `LevelFilter`, and `LogRecord` is now `Record`.
   370Ôćĺ* The `MaxLogLevelFilter` object has been removed in favor of a `set_max_level` free function.
   371Ôćĺ* The `set_logger` free functions have been restructured. The logger is now directly passed to the
   372Ôćĺ    functions rather than a closure which returns the logger. `set_logger` now takes a `&'static
   373Ôćĺ    Log` and is usable in `no_std` contexts in place of the old `set_logger_raw`. `set_boxed_logger`
   374Ôćĺ    is a convenience function which takes a `Box<Log>` but otherwise acts like `set_logger`. It
   375Ôćĺ    requires the `std` feature.
   376Ôćĺ* The `file` and `module_path` values in `Record` no longer have the `'static` lifetime to support
   377Ôćĺ    integration with other logging frameworks that don't provide a `'static` lifetime for the
   378Ôćĺ    equivalent values.
   379Ôćĺ* The `file`, `line`, and `module_path` values in `Record` are now `Option`s to support integration
   380Ôćĺ    with other logging frameworks that don't provide those values.
   382Ôćĺ### In the Future
   383Ôćĺ
   384Ôćĺ* We're looking to add support for *structured* logging - the inclusion of extra key-value pairs of
   385Ôćĺ    information in a log event in addition to the normal string message. This should be able to be
   386Ôćĺ    added in a backwards compatible manner to the 0.4.x series when the design is worked out.
   388Ôćĺ## Older
   389Ôćĺ
   390ÔćĺLook at the [release tags] for information about older releases.
README.md
     1Ôćĺlog
     3Ôćĺ
     4ÔćĺA Rust library providing a lightweight logging *facade*.
    19Ôćĺ## Minimum supported `rustc`
    20Ôćĺ
    21Ôćĺ`1.68.0+`
    25Ôćĺ## Usage
    26Ôćĺ
    27Ôćĺ### In libraries
    28Ôćĺ
    29ÔćĺLibraries should link only to the `log` crate, and use the provided macros to
    30Ôćĺlog whatever information will be useful to downstream consumers:
    58Ôćĺ### In executables
    59Ôćĺ
    60ÔćĺIn order to produce log output, executables have to use a logger implementation compatible with the facade.
    61ÔćĺThere are many available implementations to choose from, here are some options:
   106Ôćĺ## Structured logging
